This README file contains information on the contents of the
rpi3-bt-support layer.

Please see the corresponding sections below for details.

Summary
============
This layer support the initializing of bluetooth on raspberrypi3 with sysvinit.


Dependencies
============

This layer depends on:

  URI: git://git.yoctoproject.org/meta-raspberrypi
  branch: master


Patches
=======

Please submit any patches against the rpi3-bt-support layer to 
the maintainer:

Maintainer: Yusuke MITSUKI <mickey.happyglucky@gmail.com>


Adding the rpi3-bt-support layer to your build
=================================================

In order to use this layer, you need to make the build system aware of
it.

Assuming the rpi3-bt-support layer exists at the top-level of your
yocto build tree, you can add it to the build system by adding the
location of the rpi3-bt-support layer to bblayers.conf, along with any
other layers needed. e.g.:

  BBLAYERS ?= " \
    /path/to/yocto/meta \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-poky \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-yocto-bsp \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-raspberrypi \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-rpi3-bt-support \
    "

